    <group>
      <pb facs="#L1916_32_img_35" n="35"/>
      <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
        <!-- issue to resolve with a previous process? -->
        <body>
          <opener>
            <address>
              <addrLine>"Glengariff"</addrLine>
              <addrLine>Rudgrave Square,</addrLine>
              <addrLine>Egremont,</addrLine>
              <addrLine>Cheshire.</addrLine>
            </address>
            <dateline>
              <date>Feb 14 &#8212; 1916</date>
            </dateline>
            <salute>Darling Pierce</salute>
          </opener>
          <p>Many happy returns <lb/> of the day! I am at a <lb/> loss to know what to send <lb/>
            you; but I think this <lb/> little gold safety pin, with <lb/> a real ruby, will come
            <lb/> in handy, &amp; will not get <lb/> lost so easily as the <lb/> ordinary pin. They
            are <lb/> much worn here. </p>
          <pb n="34" facs="#L1916_32_img_34"/>
          <p>We have queer times <lb/>here now. Darkness <lb/> every where for fear of the <lb/>
            <del>bogie</del> "bogie man overhead". <lb/> Not a gas jet in the <lb/> streets, &amp;
            the houses all <lb/> blinded up. </p>
          <p>Oh dear! What a <lb/> time it is! Conscription <lb/> commences in March <lb/>&amp; all
            must come in <lb/> married &amp; single of <lb/>fighting age. </p>
          <cb/>
          <p>I predict that John <lb/> Castlereagh is going <lb/>in for a title. </p>
          <p>God bless you my <lb/>darling boy, &amp; may every <lb/>blessing &amp; grace be yours. </p>
          <p>Take care of your health.</p>
          <closer>
            <salute>Fond love from</salute>
            <signed>Mother</signed>
          </closer>
        </body>
      </text>
    </group>
